bFZxobDqBS1bdBtKPE4rhYSuJ6_FJR2hhOfo_anwpL__00DmKbz_j4rkF70ic487-iPnSyqknI5Whmx6c6yUyGFQzZ_awTBY3dLdJQUfKT7n1FcaVgtT0Cle7yTKrYaGoWv0d0EGc7pnPnww4tNogKH9f3lbIs91JiSrPMGI0UxiplXgU_LVuFBY0sWG7MAy9Cxx1egY38MZwyOnWVGv0DLLhbpLw3yZco1NEAD8gWafjVaXHQ80Y4DkReJwQ-GomWIC9Q0PLqJkwuObgV5o5M1ix4bHu-6ToURfdu8XHF75nvtcupD-0VwIcYBFrAWomNeETtZv0arjdEAmg7SVTn4bqnX7Qebk533jRwt0LztxnhnI9PN-hn_Vjw7PGGzi2vNQJ6BXE9UzKc5rdK6nnbDiY6-FNVkr-q4-KXLD0ubjOFD3zMln1XnVlpRq5FQT2u4FvMFK0KaSrhncPZ6gxzcBzmV33UmHiJKZh48jmlmcUq8-pQUZOLKKkxzavmhYeBZCJ_aCwtT_tLI6YLRwfMGSxlLZyz-D5JsWOPrLjRbkX5dN45mIEVJTDlhBUBlVc7ou_yNVnLo76EZ1hzTkyP07Vy93t6xMRXLvGVORxFkEhiU2KwRaU-9HmHRqZmIGD65KW8RVEsBLDn5UQGCetVqWC9G_WARCgbPkgQTt1qJ-FshiaYPVNqTzbEqRc0L6pMZLkUmJ179B8ReLCvspl16ntrZRZvJ8y9QISoh0lNIDcnrb2ZukXnus2pf91xAsrEyV2Kr4cD8ro0qRON3XwzLaMz2Wo6T0VO73tqrnNKRW7DvU8jbEQIvCsaBGumMPrWMt17allHg8p4WD4Jyre14SN_1FrXnOmpS8zMjAo-Yh64-v9Xh0wqxzozpUt9wZK2XFcaXt8fQFTejV5YV-zc5gaFJ2vjwcwdYITJJgZ_oJwxlukgNWFdzCUCUZi_KlpfJPrOmAfNKgsWDz4WrHQxpxNPwrO4pimWB1zdPPWnwWckHZSdjFsho-atQG7i1X0aeGPMq4ahWJLRFU7evT_2yg0u9oc5FKAzdi_svA5jJAm39XdBuBcabGyRZfO9hWqOZU2nHQ6Kay4c8xT3jBluSTexxI5NHFUyvR0pVUEIoc7dvzm05rWteNLHvp1jBC7gQopV7ODhKBQA4Xd6T6eDsAU6BmGDTeDMcSPLw5VteN84lPNOwhiCRFVk8Q==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether I can create an interface in the test class loader to load a helper class from the system. If that helper references ByteBuddy classes, it might end up using parent classes instead of child ones. But, can I define helper bytes in the child class loader? I wonder if I should compile a class that implements Runnable and references ByteBuddy types as part of the test sources. I need to ensure everything is set up correctly!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering classloader dynamics**\\n\\nI’m focusing on a test package helper class. Since it uses a child-first loader for org.assertj, it might load its own copy. This references org.assertj ByteBuddy, so the child-first loader pulls from the assertj jar. It implements java.lang.Runnable, which is good to keep in mind. I need dynamic access in the child class loader. To run the helper, I should set a system property for ByteBuddy, check if ClassInjector is available, and maybe install a SecurityManager afterwards.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Diagnosing code issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the need for handling the case where Legacy Injection is unavailable. It seems that using an unsafe override could potentially lead to a failure with an error message like \\\"Cannot get defined package...\\\" which sounds similar to an existing issue. But our main goal here is to ensure that our test remains focused. I need to dig deeper into the root cause to avoid complications moving forward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering nested classes**\\n\\nI'm thinking through the nested class structure here. The child-first load is interesting, especially since the parent has already loaded the outer test. When calling loadClass for the nested class, it makes sense to use the URL prefix for finding the class. I wonder if I need to ensure it has the NestHost attribute for accessing private members. Keeping the helper self-contained with public static nested classes seems like a smart approach too!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qqReMgtVKZL6MU1Ytp4aSroN|fc_0cc0101d1dece1b4016a25f89ef7d881938ee4653dcb082c33", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.assertj/assertj-core/3.22.0/src/test/java/org_assertj/assertj_core/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_assertj.assertj_core;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions;\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.ByteBuddy;\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ClassInjector;\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ClassLoadingStrategy;\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.PackageDefinitionStrategy;\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.PackageDefinitionStrategy.Definition;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest {\n    private static final String LEGACY_INJECTION_UNAVAILABLE_PREFIX = \"Cannot \";\n\n    @Test\n    void classInjectionUsesUnsafeOverrideDispatcherWhenUnsafeInjectorWasInitializedUnavailable() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            runIsolatedExercise();\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException exception) {\n            if (!isLegacyInjectionUnavailable(exception)) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void runIsolatedExercise() throws Exception {\n        URL testClassesUrl = codeSourceUrl(ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.class);\n        URL assertjCoreUrl = codeSourceUrl(Assertions.class);\n        try (ChildFirstUrlClassLoader classLoader = new ChildFirstUrlClassLoader(\n                new URL[] { testClassesUrl, assertjCoreUrl })) {\n            Class<?> exerciseClass = classLoader.loadClass(IsolatedUsingUnsafeOverrideExercise.class.getName());\n            Runnable exercise = (Runnable) exerciseClass.getConstructor().newInstance();\n         