er run after the code is done and allows all. There's another concern with the VM property being set to safe, which is global. If parallel JUnit tests run, this setting may affect other tests. I think it’s important to isolate the child to minimize the impact during that short window.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_oHpw9wKdFzpTJ9SOgeLzCyyX|fc_0cc0101d1dece1b4016a25f9294ebc8193b0afde837c539383", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.assertj/assertj-core/3.22.0/src/test/java/org_assertj/assertj_core/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        try {\n            runIsolatedExercise();\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException exception) {", "newText": "        try {\n            runExercise();\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException exception) {"}, {"oldText": "    private static void runIsolatedExercise() throws Exception {\n        Class<?> testClass = ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.class;\n        URL testClassesUrl = codeSourceUrl(testClass);\n        URL assertjCoreUrl = codeSourceUrl(Assertions.class);", "newText": "    private static void runExercise() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            runIsolatedExercise();\n        } catch (IllegalStateException exception) {\n            if (!isCodeSourceUnavailable(exception)) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n            new IsolatedUsingUnsafeOverrideExercise().run();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void runIsolatedExercise() throws Exception {\n        Class<?> testClass = ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.class;\n        URL testClassesUrl = codeSourceUrl(testClass);\n        URL assertjCoreUrl = codeSourceUrl(Assertions.class);"}, {"oldText": "    private static boolean isLegacyInjectionUnavailable(UnsupportedOperationException exception) {\n        String message = exception.getMessage(