[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating potential issues**\n\nI'm identifying several potential issues regarding class loading between child and parent classes. If the child loads a nested helper, it might resolve to a different ClassInjector due to its package prefix. Then there’s the idea of an empty public constructor—if I don’t define one, does the class automatically get a public default constructor? This may trigger checkstyle warnings. I see existing tests with private empty constructors, leading me to think about whether empty methods need comments for clarity.\n\n**Analyzing potential exceptions**\n\nI'm considering whether a general message like \"Cannot\" could obscure the specific UnsupportedOperationException (UOE) from System.setSecurityManager. I think of a clearer message, perhaps stating, \"The Security Manager is deprecated...\" since I notice that there are no caught UOE errors. The ByteBuddy generation does have a known UOE with the message \"Cannot define class using reflection.\" While a broad message is useful, it might mask unrelated UOE issues, which I need to be wary of.\n\n**Evaluating security permissions**\n\nI'm considering a potential issue with the SecurityManager and its parent application regarding the permission for codeSource. It's installed in a helper run after the code is done and allows all. There's another concern with the VM property being set to safe, which is global. If parallel JUnit tests run, this setting may affect other tests. I think it’s important to isolate the child to minimize the impact during that short window.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cc0101d1dece1b4016a25f8f243448193895123c5eccccb1f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJfkpzfJnJGpIeeRyKP6ldPYk9Z0NoCuMhCj4u-1RfzFdysgJLtF_2XnVXd161ztw2-kEjNnjKzqyqNVCl1dfVq0pkCjo0WibTGgundkS1SxBLeW6OcgT-Nx5bflcMiYyMWnPFt2Q5iiDdIfghFL-8qHsh04pTK-dwLqbLgf