ey reach uncovered dynamic-access call sites while ensuring coverage does not decrease. I need to think about isolation here. Previously, tests had no coverage but didn’t cause issues. To cover active tests while keeping the same classloader, I’d need to set UsingUnsafe as unavailable before UsingReflection. Unfortunately, this means the UsingUnsafeInjection path won’t execute in the same JVM. It seems covering UsingUnsafeInjection first isn't really possible either. I need to figure out a better approach!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring custom class loading**\\n\\nI’m considering creating a custom `URLClassLoader` to load instrumented AssertJ classes from the Gradle transformed classpath instead of from the original jar. But first, I need to check if there’s an instrumented jar available in the build. I’ll have to search for that to ensure I’m on the right track. It’s important to get this part right to avoid any issues later on!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_4nDsVCMZ4TNyeGyMDDDO5IJi|fc_0cc0101d1dece1b4016a25fa1f80348193a751837c4a5d9abc", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.assertj/assertj-core/3.22.0/build -type f \\( -name '*assertj*jar' -o -name '*assertj*class' \\) | head -50 && find tests/src/org.assertj/assertj-core/3.22.0/build -type d | grep -i instrument | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 553, "output": 1571, "cacheRead": 63488, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 65612, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780873723615, "responseId": "resp_0cc0101d1dece1b4016a25f9fcaa8c819389e17e811e6401be"}}
